-- News Corp says a Dow Jones deal won't hurt buybacks
-- 
-- Wed May 9, 2007 9:05am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/09/us-newscorp-buyback-idUSWEN789820070509

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - News Corp NWSa.N said on Wednesday its program of buying back company shares won't be affected even if it succeeds in a $5 billion bid to buy Wall Street Journal publisher Dow Jones & Co DJ.N . 

 "We can absolutely afford to reactivate our buyback and we intend to do so," News Corp Chairman and Chief Executive Rupert Murdoch said on a call with analysts to discuss quarterly results. News Corp. said that as of May 9, the company had purchased more than $3.3 billion of its stock under a $6 billion buyback program. The company said in a statement that it expects to complete the remaining purchases by May 2008, but that the program could be suspended or discontinued at any time.